<%# Phase 27 §01c-v2 — Outer Genres shelf (nested).
    Supersedes the v1 flat-tile design. The outer shelf is a single
    `<section data-shelf="outer-genres">` carrying an `<h2>` heading;
    inside it iterates one sub-shelf per genre that owns at least one
    game (alphabetical, case-insensitive). Each sub-shelf is a row of
    `Games::CoverComponent` tiles at `:shelf` variant.

    Empty buckets are hidden — when no genre owns any game, the entire
    `<section>` is suppressed (no muted placeholder, no `<h2>`). This
    intentionally reverses 01c-v1 (which always rendered a "(no genres
    yet)" placeholder) per the 01c-v2 locked decision #7.

    The 01c-v2 spec calls for a `Game#primary_genre_id` pointer so a
    multi-genre game appears under exactly one genre's sub-shelf. The
    migration is out of scope for this implementation pass (parent
    dispatch — "no new migrations"); the partial falls back to the
    existing `genre.games` association. A multi-genre game therefore
    appears in every sub-shelf its `game_genres` join touches. The
    fallback is documented; the surface stays correct end-to-end and
    the primary-genre migration is a follow-up.

    Locals:
      genres  ActiveRecord::Relation of Genre rows, pre-filtered by the
              caller to only include genres that own at least one game
              and pre-ordered alphabetical case-insensitive.
      batch   Optional `Games::GenreShelfBatch` carrying pre-fetched
              `{ count:, games: }` slices per genre (P27 reviewer
              follow-up #2). When absent, each sub-shelf falls back to
              its in-partial count + fetch (kept for view-spec
              isolation; the controller passes the batch in prod).
%>
<%
  genres = local_assigns.fetch(:genres)
  # Prefer an explicit `batch:` local (used by isolated view specs),
  # else read the controller-assigned `@genres_shelf_batch` so the
  # production codepath does not require an edit to `index.html.erb`
  # (owned by sibling agent).
  batch  = local_assigns[:batch] || @genres_shelf_batch
%>
<% if genres.any? %>
  <section class="shelf shelf--genres outer-shelf" data-shelf="outer-genres" style="margin-top: 16px;">
    <%# Phase 27 polish (2026-05-11) — hairline between consecutive
        sub-shelves moved to `app/assets/tailwind/application.css`
        (Fix 4, 2026-05-11). The CSS selector
        `section[data-shelf="outer-genres"] > section.sub-shelf:not(:first-of-type)`
        is preserved verbatim in the stylesheet. %>
    <%# 2026-05-11 polish (Fix 1) — the outer `<h2>genres</h2>` heading
        was retired. The page now opens straight into the genre
        sub-shelves; the per-sub-shelf `<h3>` headings carry the genre
        name. The outer `<section>` still wraps the iteration so the
        sub-shelf hairline CSS scope (`section[data-shelf="outer-genres"]`)
        keeps working. %>
    <% genres.each do |genre| %>
      <% if batch %>
        <%= render "games/genre_sub_shelf", genre: genre, batch_slice: batch.for(genre) %>
      <% else %>
        <%= render "games/genre_sub_shelf", genre: genre %>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>
  </section>
<% end %>
